The paper deals with the problem of detecting early-stage infection in an enterprise setting using large-scale log data. This involves the use of machine learning techniques and graph theory to detect malware and advanced persistent threats (APTs) that evade traditional security products. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
